change of the innermost radius, while the innermost radius remained
constant during the type-B QPO detections at 1.6-4.1 Hz. Hence, we
suggest that the origin of the type-B QPOs is different from that of
type-C QPOs, the latter of which would originate from the disk
truncation radius. Assuming the constant innermost radius in the latter
phase of the outburst as the innermost stable circular orbit, the black
hole mass in MAXI J1659-152 is estimated to be 3.6-8.0M$_{&sun;}$
for a distance of 5.3-8.6 kpc and an inclination angle of
