$_{sup}${\gt}10$^{10}$ M $_{sun}$from host galaxies to
CNDs, because the final BH mass is only 1\%-10\% of the total supplied
mass from QSO hosts. (2) High star formation efficiency for a rapid BH
growth which is comparable to high-z starburst galaxies such as
submillimeter galaxies. We also find that if the BH growth is limited by
the Eddington accretion, the final BH mass is greatly suppressed when
the period of mass supply from hosts, t $_{sup}$, is shorter than
