morphology is predicted for CSOs and FR II galaxies. This seems to be
consistent with the higher fraction of distorted morphology of MSOs than
that of CSOs and FR II galaxies. Finally, we predict that only CSOs
whose initial advance speed is higher than about 0.1 c can evolve into
FR II galaxies, comparing the hot spot speed with the sound speed of the
