regions, in a different way from the expectation by the standard biased
galaxy formation scenario. In addition, we make a prediction for the
angular correlation function of LAEs at redshifts higher than 3. It is
found that the prediction deviates from that made by the standard biased
galaxy formation scenario even at redshifts 4 {\lt}\~{} z {\lt}\~{} 6.
}},
