angular resolution image (sigma FWHM =13'') at 150 GHz reveals complex
morphological structures of the cluster region, which cannot be simply
described by the spherical isothermal beta-model. If such inhomogeneous
morphological features prove to be generic for high-redshift clusters,
distance measurements to the clusters based on their Sunyaev-Zel'dovich
data with low angular resolution imaging should be interpreted with
caution.
}},
